cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SI 

This paper proposes a machine learning-based approach for automated classification of heart sound recordings. The use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for feature learning and classification suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). However, the focus on heart diseases and the use of physiological data suggest that cs.SI is less likely than the other four sub-categories.
